(460, 3,N'R&C Rift Apart looks absolutely stunning, and has very fun and fluid combat with an amazing lineup of weapons; my favourites being the Enforcer, Blackhole Storm and Cold Snap. The haptic feedback with the weapons all feel great, especially with the Enforcer (I always love a good shotgun). There’s lots of neat level designs and environments that caught me off guard, and were very enjoyable to play. The story was entertaining enough but is forgettable, the  best parts involving the conflicts between the main villains, and gets quite funny at times. After being quite critical on future era, I think this is definitely a step forward for the Ratchet & Clank franchise.',N'2024-02-26'),
