(737, 0,N'Its not exactly the best JRPG ever what with its flaws in certain routes and its archaic JRPG convention that holds it back, but its one that resonate with me the most. Its unique format of multiple short stories is smth ive never seen in JRPGs before and they pull off the concept with flying colors. Its a game brimming with innovation in each part of its storytelling, capped off with a final route that manages to tie all its other routes together and deliver its own beautiful story. And all this was done in a 90s JRPG released on the Super Famicom. Incredible. Its a must-play to anyone who considers themselves JRPG fan and want to see smth new in this genre',N'2024-03-21'),
