(1013, 1,N'Another great tale of two brothers from Josef Fares. The story is pretty barebones and unspecial throughout but it’s all tied together with a pretty great and unforeseen conclusion. The two main characters are really nice, having sort of a True Detective-protag style bond that sees you slowly care for each other more as the chaos intensifies. Gameplay widely varies from small minigames to stealth sections to QTE-mania to full-on cover shooter, like a more scatterbrained version of A Plague Tale which wouldn’t come out for another year. As scatterbrained as it seems, it still all comes together to create a pretty semi-unique experience. The aesthetic of the game is also pretty good, feeling like an anachronistic mashup of the 1970s and modern day, until you find out for sure that it’s the 1970s.',N'2025-01-05'),
